How to integrate jenkins with Github:

Continous Download:

1.create a free style job
2.Install github and git plugin
2.Source code Management-git
3.Enter repository url of github which is to be download continously.
4.Go to managed jenkins->configure credentials for github
5.Build trigger-->GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling.
    This allows Jenkins to build automatically when it receives a webhook notification from GitHub.
6.setup webhook->add webhook->payload url(jenkins server in manage jenkins->system)
7.Set Content type to application/json
8.Choose the event triggers:
    Recommended: Just the push event.
9.Click Add Webhook.
